  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into chips</p><p>Add the <strong>chips</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 25-30 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1647248604963-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1647248604963-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1647248604963-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1647248604963-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1647248604963-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the chips are in the oven, slice<strong> </strong>your <strong>tomato[es] </strong>into 1 round per person</p><p>Roughly chop the <strong>remaining tomato</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>tomato rounds </strong>and<strong> chopped tomato</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>rice vinegar</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and<strong> sugar</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and set aside – this is your <strong>quick-pickled tomato</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1647248608133-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1647248608133-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1647248608133-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1647248608133-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1647248608133-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely grate your <strong>garlic</strong> and <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>beef mince </strong>to a bowl with the<strong> grated garlic</strong> and <strong>ginger</strong> and season with<strong> </strong>a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Using clean hands, give everything a good mix up until fully combined, then roll the<strong> mince </strong>into 1 <strong>meatball</strong> per person and press down with your hands to form a patty – this is your <strong>beef patty[ies]</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1647248611711-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1647248611711-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1647248611711-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1647248611711-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1647248611711-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> smoked streaky bacon</strong> to one side of a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined tray (or two!)</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 10 min or until beginning to crisp up</p><p>Drain your <strong>mozzarella</strong>, then pat and squeeze as much liquid out as you can with kitchen paper and tear into rough, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Wash, then remove 1 <strong>leaf</strong> from the<strong> lettuce</strong> per person and set aside, shred the <strong>inner core[s]</strong> and pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1647248615917-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1647248615917-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1647248615917-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1647248615917-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1647248615917-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a high heat, add the<strong> beef patty[ies]</strong>, press down firmly with a spatula and cook for 5 min (cooking for 5? You may need to do this in batches!)</p><p>Reduce the heat to medium-high, then flip and top the <strong>patty[ies]</strong> with most of your <strong>gochujang paste</strong> (can’t handle the heat? Go easy!) and the <strong>torn mozzarella</strong> then cook, covered, for 5 min further or until the patty[ies] is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the cheese has melted</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1647248619161-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1647248619161-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1647248619161-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1647248619161-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1647248619161-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once crispy, remove the bacon from the oven, pour your <strong>honey</strong> all over, then sprinkle <strong>half</strong> your <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>sesame seeds</strong> (save the rest for garnish!) on top – this is your<strong> candied sesame bacon</strong></p><p>Slice your<strong> brioche bun[s]</strong> in half and add, cut side up, to the other side of the baking tray[s]</p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for 2-3 min or until the brioche is toasted and the bacon has started to caramelise</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Use a separate tray!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1647248623857-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1647248623857-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1647248623857-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1647248623857-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1647248623857-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Separate the <strong>quick-pickled tomato rounds </strong>(save them for the burgers!) from the quick-pickled chopped tomatoes and set aside</p><p>Drain away 2/3<strong> </strong>of the <strong>pickling liquid </strong>and add the <strong>remaining gochujang paste </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) and <strong>half</strong> of your <strong>mayo </strong>(save the rest for later!)</p><p>Add the <strong>shredded lettuce</strong> and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>tangy tomato salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1647248626881-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1647248626881-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1647248626881-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1647248626881-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1647248626881-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Spread each<strong> toasted brioche half </strong>with the <strong>remaining mayo</strong>, then sandwich with a<strong> lettuce leaf</strong>, <strong>cheesy gochujang patty</strong>, <strong>candied sesame bacon</strong>, and a <strong>quick-pickled tomato round</strong> – this is your <strong>Korean-style beef & candied sesame bacon burger</strong></p><p>Serve the<strong> tangy tomato salad</strong> and<strong> chips </strong>to the side, sprinkling the<strong> remaining toasted sesame seeds</strong> all over</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
